</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35FC4C6FFC8FF96FF47AB8E7C8B4939" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFA974DFFC8FF97FF47AB8E7BFC4CCE" blockId="2.[151,1437,1220,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Female. General coloration yellow with head and thorax brown spotted. Head nearly as bulky as thorax (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC8FF97FAB1AB8E7EA64E29" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,272,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,594,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,589,1784]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 1, head, frontal view; 2, head, lateral view; 3, head, dorsal view; 4, antennae; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, thorax, lateral view; 7, wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186178/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Figs. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC8FF97FF47ABA07EA64E29" box="[151,198,1258,1284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frons yellow with brown spots at base of anterior prominence and at apex, near antennae. Frons with small yellow lateroclinate setae laterally, and with rather deep incised median line and dark brown to black bifid prominence anteriorly. Ocelli absent. Ocellar tubercle slightly protuberant with distinct tuft of brown setae. Postcranium yellow with yellow setae, brown spotted dorsally and ventrally, with longer setae on dorsal brown spot. No series of postocular setae can be distinguished from occipital setulae. Lunule large, subshining, distinctly small setulose. Antennal sockets separated by node-like carina. Face yellow, margined with brown ventrally, with median sclerotized zone more or less differentiated from lateral zones that are transparent and converge near antennal sockets. Eye brown-reddish, large, with small subequal facets. Antenna very short (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC8FF97FE5DA96A7FB84D17" box="[397,472,1568,1594]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,272,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,594,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,589,1784]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 1, head, frontal view; 2, head, lateral view; 3, head, dorsal view; 4, antennae; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, thorax, lateral view; 7, wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186178/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC8FF97FE16A96A7FB84D17" box="[454,472,1568,1594]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pedicel with anterodorsal protuberance with long and distinct setae. Flagellum with deep depression in which arista is inserted. Arista very complex, with dendritic branching (fan-shaped). Mouthparts entirely absent. Thorax (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC8FF97FD8AA9277CAF4DAA" box="[602,719,1645,1671]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,272,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,594,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,589,1784]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 1, head, frontal view; 2, head, lateral view; 3, head, dorsal view; 4, antennae; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, thorax, lateral view; 7, wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186178/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Figs. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC8FF97FD70A9277CAF4DAA" box="[672,719,1645,1671]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
</figureCitation>
) mainly yellow, with brown margin on mesonotum, entire scutellum, and extreme dorsal and ventral parts of mesopleuron. Mesoscutum with numerous short yellow reclinate setulae, and erect supra-alar and postalar tuft of dense dark setulae. Notopleuron bare. Scutellum with numerous yellow setulae dorsally, and one pair of dense and dark setulae posteriorly. Proepisternum and proepimeron bare. Prothoracic spiracles rounded, almost bare. Postpronotal lobe with two small setae. Posterodorsal margin of anepisternum, median part of anepimeron and katepisternum setulose. Legs (only right fore leg, except tarsi, and right hind leg present) yellow, but fore coxa brown anteriorly. Legs elongate, with small setae. Fore and hind tibiae without apical spurs. 
<collectingCountry id="F352D7DDFFC8FF97FCBDA8367DC94CBB" box="[877,937,1916,1942]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur attenuated distally and hind tibiae attenuated basally. Wing (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC8FF97FE15A8E87C6B4C91" box="[453,523,1954,1980]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,272,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,594,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,589,1784]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 1, head, frontal view; 2, head, lateral view; 3, head, dorsal view; 4, antennae; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, thorax, lateral view; 7, wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186178/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC8FF97FE2CA8E87C6B4C91" box="[508,523,1954,1980]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) narrowed basally, without alula. Veins yellow, membrane yellow basally and along costal margin, the remaining part hyaline. Costa with subcostal break. Costal vein extending to vein M.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA974DFFC9FF96FF47AFD27C8B4939" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Sc vein incomplete. Vein R 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FE06AFE27FBE4B9B" box="[470,478,168,182]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
with sparse, weak setulae. Cell r 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FCB0AFE27D084B9B" box="[864,872,168,182]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
with four distinct crossveins forming five small closed cells; the first hyaline window in this cell at least 3.5x longer than other hyaline windows. Crossvein rm near the middle of cell dm and at level of vein R 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FCCFAFB27D474A2B" box="[799,807,248,262]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
. Anal vein (A) incomplete. Base of vein M rather evanescent leaving cell bm open anteriorly. Abdomen yellow, rather oval. Tergites (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC9FF96FB3CAE587B5C4A01" box="[1260,1340,274,300]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[269,1322,544,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1323,542,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 8, abdomen, dorsal view; 9, abdomen, ventral view; 10, distal abdominal segment, lateral view; 11, cerci, ventral view; 12, internal egg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186179/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FAFCAE587B5C4A01" box="[1324,1340,274,300]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) rather membranous; tergite 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FE5FAE727FFE4A7F" box="[399,414,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
more sclerotized laterally; tergite 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FCE0AE727D5E4A7F" box="[816,830,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="6.0">6</number>
reduced to tranverse line of setae. Sternites (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC9FF96FA9DAE727BF24A7F" box="[1357,1426,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[269,1322,544,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1323,542,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 8, abdomen, dorsal view; 9, abdomen, ventral view; 10, distal abdominal segment, lateral view; 11, cerci, ventral view; 12, internal egg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186179/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FA53AE727BF24A7F" box="[1411,1426,312,338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) more membranous than tergites. Sternite 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FDA9AE157CE84A54" box="[633,648,351,377]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
V-shaped. Sternite 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FCBDAE157D1C4A54" box="[877,892,351,377]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
distinct and remaining sternites distinguisable only by clusters of setae. Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC9FF96FD8AAECF7CB94AB2" box="[602,729,389,415]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[269,1322,544,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1323,542,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 8, abdomen, dorsal view; 9, abdomen, ventral view; 10, distal abdominal segment, lateral view; 11, cerci, ventral view; 12, internal egg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186179/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Figs. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FD4EAECF7CB94AB2" box="[670,729,389,415]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="9.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="8.0">8–11</number>
</figureCitation>
) with segment 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FC42AECF7DC14AB2" box="[914,929,389,415]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="7.0">7</number>
enlarged, well sclerotized, not completely fused laterally (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC9FF96FE80AEE67FF84AEB" box="[336,408,428,454]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[269,1322,544,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1323,542,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 8, abdomen, dorsal view; 9, abdomen, ventral view; 10, distal abdominal segment, lateral view; 11, cerci, ventral view; 12, internal egg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186179/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FE58AEE67FF84AEB" box="[392,408,428,454]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Distal eversible tube membranous with two more slender parts, the first representing segment 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FED2AE997F734AC0" box="[258,275,467,493]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="8.0">8</number>
; distal segment wider distally (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC9FF96FD5BAE997C844AC0" box="[651,740,467,493]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[269,1322,544,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1323,542,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 8, abdomen, dorsal view; 9, abdomen, ventral view; 10, distal abdominal segment, lateral view; 11, cerci, ventral view; 12, internal egg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186179/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FD14AE997C844AC0" box="[708,740,467,493]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
), with short, setulose, and quite blunt fused cerci dorsally (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC9FF96FF4FAEB07F4E4939" box="[159,302,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[269,1322,544,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1323,542,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 8, abdomen, dorsal view; 9, abdomen, ventral view; 10, distal abdominal segment, lateral view; 11, cerci, ventral view; 12, internal egg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186179/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Figs. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FF32AEB07F4E4939" box="[226,302,506,532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Internal eggs as illustrated (
<figureCitation id="137E8BC8FFC9FF96FD56AEB07CBE4939" box="[646,734,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[269,1322,544,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1323,542,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 8, abdomen, dorsal view; 9, abdomen, ventral view; 10, distal abdominal segment, lateral view; 11, cerci, ventral view; 12, internal egg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186179/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D856AFFC9FF96FD6DAEB07CBE4939" box="[701,734,506,532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
